<HEADLINE> Bosnia, Yugoslavia to Establish Diplomatic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Bosnia-Herzegovina and the Federal
Republic of Yugoslavia have decided to establish diplomatic
relations, French President Jacques Chirac announced today.
</P>
<P>
The two countries will soon exchange ambassadors, said Chirac
at a joint press conference with Bosnian President Alija
Izetbegovic and Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic, who held
their first summit meeting here today.
</P>
<P>
Bosnia and the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, which is
composed of Serbia and Montenegro, were parts of the former
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The two countries had bad relations during the Bosnian civil
war as Serbia allegedly supported the rebel Bosnian Serbs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
