<HEADLINE> Bush Fire Threatens Kruger National Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Johannesburg, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A raging bush fire has
devastated at least a quarter of South Africa's premier tourist
attraction, the Kruger National Park.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of animals and birds are feared dead in the
conflagration in the southern part of the park, the South African
Press Association reported today.
</P>
<P>
The park draws 700,000 foreign tourists a year.
</P>
<P>
The blaze, which was still burning this morning, was sparked
by lightning one week ago.
</P>
<P>
Park officials said the blaze was made worse by this week's
high temperatures and gale-force winds.
</P>
<P>
The park, founded in 1926, covers 20,000 square kilometres and
is one of the greatest diversity of wildlife in the world. enditem

=10031554

=10031557
NNNN
23:56 23:56 g # PAB
</P>
