<HEADLINE> Indian President Visits Oman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Indian President Shankar
Dayal Sharma arrived today in Muscat, the capital of Oman, for an
official four-day visit, a report reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Omani head of state Sultan Qaboos Bin Said greeted the Indian
president at the Muscat airport.
</P>
<P>
The Indian president's visit to Oman aims to strengthen
bilateral relations and expand the scope of economic cooperation
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He will also discuss with Omani officials the establishment of
an economic grouping of the countries overlooking the Indian
Ocean. 
</P>
