<HEADLINE> China Selects Students to Study Overseas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 3 (Xinhua) -- About 1,400 Chinese people will
be able to study abroad with government aid after successfully
competing under a new and open system for government-supported
overseas study.
</P>
<P>
They have become the first group of the students to win the
honor since China launched a new system in January to encourage
fair competition in selecting excellent students for overseas
study.
</P>
<P>
The 1,399 people are expected to be sent to study in 53
countries after signing agreements with the State Foundation for
Overseas Study, a governmental organ which will fund their study
abroad.
</P>
<P>
All those selected will be visiting scholars, including 28
percent who will be senior scholars. And 68 percent have earned
master's or doctoral degrees.
</P>
<P>
The new system was highly welcomed when it was announced early
this year. Thousands of people from across the country asked for
application forms.
</P>
<P>
Under the system, applicants are evaluated by experts organized
by the foundation, and are finally selected by the State Education
Commission.
</P>
<P>
They are required to sign agreements with the administrative
committee of the foundation to make sure that they return to
China. Otherwise they have to pay compensations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
