<HEADLINE> Turkish Security Forces Seize Large Quantity of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Turkish security forces seized
12.8 kilograms of pure heroin and 286 kilograms of base morphine
in operations against the drug trafficking in Turkey, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the security forces stopped a car at
Balaban village in Gevas town in Van province, eastern Turkey,
and found 9.2 kilograms of pure heroin under the back chair of
the vehicle.
</P>
<P>
One suspected drug smuggler has been detained, said the
agency.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Gendarme soldiers searched a farmer's house in
Kumyaka village in Mudanya town in Bursa province, western
Turkey, and confiscated 286 kilograms of base morphine in nine
bags, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
Anatolia reported that Turkish police also confiscated 3.6
kilograms of heroin in the country's largest city of Istanbul
from ten Tanzanians and Nigerians, but it did not specify the
operation and the exact number of the Tanzanians and Nigerians
involved.
</P>
<P>
The drugs were transferred to Turkey from Iran and
Afghanistan, according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
