<HEADLINE> Chang, Krajicek Advance in Singapore Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Wimbledon champion Richard
Krajicek of the Netherlands crushed Australia's Patrick Rafter
6-4, 6-2 Thursday, and top seed Michael Chang also enter the
quarterfinals at the Singapore Open.
</P>
<P>
Chang, the world No. 2, routed Venezuelan Nicolas Pereira 6-3,
6-1 in 69 minutes, lobbing and hitting passing shots just out of
his opponent's reach.
</P>
<P>
The world No. 8 Krajicek fired 12 aces to Rafter's 5.
</P>
<P>
In Friday's quarterfinals, Chang meets Javier Frana of
Argentina and Krajicek faces Thomas Johansson of Sweden, who
defeated seventh seed Byron Black of Zimbabwe 6-0, 7-6 (9-7).
</P>
<P>
German Martin Sinner upset No. 4 seed Mark Woodforde of
Australia 6-2, 6-3. American Jonathan Stark served 19 aces in
beating No. 6 Sjeng Schalken of the Netherlands 7-6 (10-8), 7-5 in
one hour, 43 minutes.
</P>
<P>
In the tournament's longest match so far, Frana outplayed
France's Guillaume Raoux 6-4, 6-7 (4-7), 7-6 (7-5) in two hours,
18 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Frana, who had upset eighth seed Hendrik Dreekmann of Germany
in the first round, combined power with touch, chasing down almost
everything Raoux hit. He rifled back some brilliant passing shots,
especially on the backhand side. 
</P>
</TEXT>
