<HEADLINE> Three Gunmen Killed in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Egypt's security forces shot dead
three gunmen today in a village near Malawi, Minya province, some
220 kilometers south of Cairo.
</P>
<P>
The security forces killed the gunmen after exchanging fire
with them, according to Egypt's new agency MENA.
</P>
<P>
MENA quoted a security source as saying that a number of
unidentified gunmen opened fired from a nearby cemetery at the
security forces, who were searching in plantations near the site
where two policemen were killed by gunmen Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
The security forces returned fire and killed the three gunmen,
MENA said, adding that two automatic machine guns and a pistol
were found near the bodies of the gunmen, believed to be Moslem
militants.
</P>
<P>
Egypt's security forces have fiercely cracked down on Moslem
militants, who have waged a violent campaign against the
government since 1992 in an attempt to install strict Islamic
rule in the country.
</P>
<P>
Recently, there have been terrorist attacks by suspected
Moslem militants on police and civilians in southern Egypt almost
on daily basis.
</P>
<P>
The two policemen were believed to be killed by Moslem
militants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
