<HEADLINE> 6 Killed, 12 Injured in Mine Explosion in Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PESHAWAR, Pakistan, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Six people, including
a Taliban commander, were killed and 12 others injured in a mine
explosion in Afghanistan early this morning.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that a group of Taliban fighters
were moving on the Kabul-Jalalabad road when a mine exploded at
Tangi Abreshan near Sarobi, about 75 km east of Kabul.
</P>
<P>
The mine was planted by ex-government troops last month for
checking the advancing Taliban which captured Kabul later.
</P>
<P>
All the injured were rushed to the Sarobi hospital.  
</P>
</TEXT>
