<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambican President Leaves Angola for Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano left here for home today after attending the SADC
summit.
</P>
<P>
Chissano said at a press conference at the airport that
leaders of the Southern African Development Community (SADC)
countries will continue to make efforts for peace and stability
in the region.
</P>
<P>
He said the summit has worked out a specific program for
this purpose although Jonan Savimbi, leader of the former rebel
National Union for the Total Independence of Angola, did not
attend the summit.
</P>
<P>
A delegation, consisting of the foreign ministers of
Mozambique, Angola, Zimbabwe and South Africa, will go to New
York to report the peace process in Angola to the meeting of
the United Nations Security Council scheduled for October 11.
</P>
<P>
Chissano arrived here on Tuesday for the SADC summit.
