<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 19th Century Jewish Cemetery Desecrated in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A 19th century Jewish cemetery in
Delme, eastern France, was found to have been desecrated by
unidentified people, but police said that it could be done by
children who frequented the cemetery as a playground.
</P>
<P>
Some of the tomb stones in the cemetery were pulled down and
the inscription on one of the stones were erased by hammer, but
there was no graffito or brand of the Nazi, Agence France Presse
quoted police as saying today.
</P>
<P>
The cemetery has stopped receiving the dead since 1880, and
most of its tombs were regarded as classic monuments.
</P>
<P>
The Jewish consistory in the department of Moselle has launched
a lawsuit against the desecrators. 
</P>
</TEXT>
