<HEADLINE> S.African Police on Alert for Ivory Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The entire South African
police have been put on a nationwide alert for a large
consignment of illegal ivory believed to be orginating from
Gongo.
</P>
<P>
Pieter Lategan, chief of South African police endangered
species protection unit, told the press today that 200 elephants
were slaughtered by poachers in the central African country
recently.
</P>
<P>
A reward of more than 20,000 U.S. Dollars has been offered for
information leading to the arrest of the smugglers.
</P>
<P>
Lategan said the mass slaughter of the elephants took place
about three weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
The police chief said the smugglers might
transport the tusks by road or air to a South African port
on their way to the far east. 
</P>
