<HEADLINE> Bahrain Urges Israel to Change Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Bahrain today urged
Israel to change its policy to ensure the continuation of peace
process in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the United Nations General Assembly, Shaikh Mohamed
Bin Mubarak Al-khalifa, Minister of Foreign Affairs of the State
Bahrain, said that his country views with deep concern the serious
events occurred recently in the Middle East as a result of the
policy undertaken by the present Israeli government.
</P>
<P>
By reneging on the agreements and commitments reached within
the framework of peace process, Israel "will undoubtedly cause a
drastic setback to the peace process and lead the region back ot a
new cycle of tension and violence", he added.
</P>
<P>
He urged Israel to forswear its plans to change the Arab and
Islamic character of the city of Jerusalem and called on the
international community to pressure the Israeli government to
renounce its political concept which is based on policies of
expansion and settlement in Arab territories. 
</P>
