<HEADLINE> Rabin's Assassin, Two Accomplices Sentenced to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The District Court in Tel
Aviv, Israel, this afternoon passed sentences on former Israeli
prime minister Yitzhak Rabin's convicted assassin Yigal Amir and
his two accomplices.
</P>
<P>
Yigal Amir, his brother Haggai and their friend Dror Adani
were sentenced after the three were convicted on charges of
murdering Rabin, illegal possession of fire arms and explosives,
and conspiracy to harm Palestinians and their property, reported
Israel Radio.
</P>
<P>
A three-judge panel sentenced Yigal Amir to five years
imprisonment in addition to life sentence for murdering Rabin and
another six years for wounding Rabin's body guard. Haggai was
sentenced to 12 years in jail and Dror Adani seven years
imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
Yigal Amir, who assassinated Rabin at a peace rally in Tel
Aviv last November, said after the sentence that he was proud of
his action and regretted that he did not kill Rabin three years
ago. Haggai Amir had nothing to say. Dror Adani said that he was
innocent of all the charges against him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
