<HEADLINE> Seminar on Business Women to be Held in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A two-day seminar on
entrepreneurship development and women in Tanzania will be held in
Arusha, Northern Tanzania from October 24 to 25, this year.
</P>
<P>
The seminar, organized by the National Board of Accountants
and Auditors (NBAA), is aimed at educating and sensitizing
participants on the gender issues and entrepreneurship
development among women in the country.
</P>
<P>
NBAA Executive Director Ludovick Utuoh said here today in a
statement that during the seminar, participants would be able to
deliberate on how gender awareness in entrepreneurship can improve
business performance of women.
</P>
<P>
Also, the seminar will address on current issues like trade
liberalization, privatization, democratization and the Beijing
resolution in a transparent economy.
</P>
<P>
According to Utuoh, the target group of the seminar includes women
managers, executives, accountants, business women and policy makers.
Others are lawyers, non-governmental organizations' officials and
gender researchers.
</P>
<P>
After completion of the seminar, participants will be awarded with
prices, it is said. 
</P>
