<HEADLINE> Swazi Premier in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After having talks with Swazi Premier Sibusiso Dlamini here,
Mocumbi said the Goba road linking Swaziland with Maputo has been
rehabilitated, but a railway should also be repaired. However, he
did not say when and how it would be rehabilitated.
</P>
<P>
Mocumbi said the talks between the two sides also included
Swaziland's participation in the development of Maputo corridor
which Mozambique is developing with South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Swaziland and Zimbabwe exported 220,000 tons of sugar
through the sugar harbor of Maputo in the upper half of this
year, and will deliver another 180,000 tons later this year.
</P>
<P>
Dlamini arrived here for a one-day visit and is expected to
leave for Swaziland on Friday. 
</P>
