<HEADLINE> Hamas Calls for Military Resistance Against Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The Islamic Resistance
Movement (Hamas) issued a statement today reiterating armed
resistance against Israeli occupation, according to a report of
JMCC, a Palestinian press service based in east Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
In the statement Hamas called on the Palestinian people "to
go out after tomorrow's Friday prayers in procession and
confrontation against the enemy's forces."
</P>
<P>
The statement came in response to the Washington summit which
was attended by, among others, Palestinian Authority President
Yasser Arafat and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
"As it was expected, the self-rule authority President Yasser
Arafat failed in getting any tangible achievements for our people
albeit his previous promises," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
It described the Washington summit as a new failure on the
Oslo path, saying that Netanyahu was the "only winner" of the
summit.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that Hamas supports "continuation of
people's sacrifices and martyrdom in defending Moslem land and
their holy sites in Palestine."
</P>
<P>
It added that the popular and military resistance should be a
"Palestinian spear in confronting the Zionist plans and plots
until victory and liberation."
</P>
<P>
Hamas demanded that the self-rule authority should not
obstruct the national and Islamic forces, who are determined to
carry on military and popular resistance against Israeli
occupation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
