<HEADLINE> Angola, Portugal Sign Defense Coop Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A defense cooperation pact was
forged here today by the governments of Angola and Portugal,
signaling closer military ties between the two traditional
allies.
</P>
<P>
A joint defense committee would be created to meet annually to
discuss bilateral military cooperation, according to the pact
signed by Angolan Defense Minister Pedro Sebastiao and visiting
Portuguese Defense Minister Antonio Victorino.
</P>
<P>
And Portugal would be responsible for training military
officers for the Angola army which is soon to be formed, said the
pact.
</P>
<P>
It said the two countries would also cooperate in armament
production.
</P>
<P>
Victorino has met with a number of Angola's top military
officers to strengthen ties of cooperation since he arrived in
Luanda on Monday for a five-day official visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
