<HEADLINE> London, Paris Shares Down on US Employment Data </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Stock markets in London and Paris
failed to extend their Wednesday gains and all closed down today
as traders were cautious ahead of the U.S. September jobs data due
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The London market, the largest in Europe, had climbed to a
record high of 4,024.3 points earlier today before retreating
back and ending at the key 4,000 points level, down 15.1 points as
market players took profits after recent record breaking gains.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market had adopted a cautious stance in the
run-up to Friday's U.S. employment figures.
</P>
<P>
French shares finished the session slightly lower today after
Wednesday's strong gains, with the CAC-40 index down 5.75 points
at 2,136.09. Disappointment with some companies' half-year results
was blamed for the losses.
</P>
<P>
The Frankfurt market in Germany was closed today for a national
holiday and regular trading will resume Friday.
</P>
<P>
London's Financial Times-Stock Exchange index of 100 leading
British shares closed down 15.1 points at 4,000. In Paris, the
CAC-40 share index finished 5.75 points lower at 2,136.09. 
</P>
</TEXT>
