<HEADLINE> Nigeria Re-elected Member of International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian has been elected to
another two-year term as a member of the development committee of
the World Bank and International Monetary Fund (IMF), the News
Agency of Nigeria reported today.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria, which was re-elected at the current annual meeting of
the bank and fund in Washington, represents the Africa group one
constituency of the 24-member committee.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria was first elected into the committee in 1994 in
Madrid, Spain.
</P>
<P>
The development committee is a joint ministerial committee of
the board of governors of the World Bank and the IMF, and its
primary focus is the transfer of real resources to developing
countries.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the re-election of Nigeria as member
of the committee would afford the country ''a unique opportunity
to continue to defend and indeed advance the interests of
developing countries in general and the Africa group one
constituency in particular.'' 
</P>
