<HEADLINE> Non-Bailable Arrest Warrant Issued Against Rao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- A Delhi court today issued a
non-bailable arrest warrant on former Prime Minister P. V.
Narasimha Rao for his involvement in the St Kitts forgery case.
</P>
<P>
The case was reportedly an attempt to defame former Prime
Minister V.P. Singh and his son Ajeya Singh in 1989.
</P>
<P>
Chief Metropolitan Magistrate and additional sessions judge
Prem Kumar today took cognizance of the charge sheet filed by the
Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) last week against Rao.
</P>
<P>
The CBI in its 15-page charge sheet filed on September 26
alleged that Rao, the then external affairs minister, and others
conspired to forge documents to defame V. P. Singh by purporting
to show that his son maintained a secret account in the First
Trust Corporation in St Kitts Islands in the West Indies.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the charge sheet was filed, Rao's counsel
made an appeal to the Delhi High Court for anticipatory bail,
which, if granted, protects an accused against arrest.
</P>
<P>
Today's action by the Delhi court is another setback for Rao
who was also involved in a 100,000 U.S. dollar cheating case,
which is under trial by the Delhi High Court.  
</P>
</TEXT>
