<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People of Ethnic Hui Group Place Importance on Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- People of ethnic Hui group in
southwest China's Yunnan province realize the importance of
education for their children. And it has become their tradition to
send their children to schools.
</P>
<P>
With a population of 550,000, the people of the ethnic Hui
minorities live in 127 counties and cities in Yunnan province.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 95 percent of local Hui children of school
age are studying at schools, and 80 to 85 percent of local primary
and junior middle school students of Hui nationality go to higher
schools. The figures are the highest among 26 ethnic groups in
Yunnan.
</P>
<P>
The education of Hui people consists of two parts, education on
Islam and education conducted according to the state teaching
program, learning knowledge on natural and social sciences.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Yunnan now has some 80 Hui people studying
abroad. They mainly major in economic management, commercial
management and Arabian literature.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
