<HEADLINE> Dalian Plays Major Role in Opening Up in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Dalian, a city open to overseas
businesses, is playing an increasingly important role in promoting
the opening-up drive of Northeast China and revitalization of the
regional economy.
</P>
<P>
Half of the exports handled by Dalian port of entry and 80
percent of the cargo handled by the port are from the Northeast
China region, according to Dalian Mayor Bo Xilai.
</P>
<P>
And the total business volume of the past nine export
commodities fairs reached 4.65 billion US dollars, making Dalian a
key link in contact between Northeast China and world markets.
</P>
<P>
The mayor said the preferential policies the state has granted
to Dalian have benefited all of the northeast region.
</P>
<P>
At present other cities in Northeast China and eastern Inner
Mongolia region have opened more than 300 offices, and set up
4,100 businesses in Dalian, in which 200-plus are overseas-funded.
</P>
<P>
To fulfill its role as a window for the opening up of the
region, Dalian has set up offices in other cities in Northeast
China, and built more exhibition facilities for businesses from
other cities in the region to hold business invitation and
negotiation activities in Dalian. 
</P>
