<HEADLINE> Farmers Turn Castaway into Handicrafts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in suburban Shanghai
has found a new way to make money, by turning vegetable leaves
into handicraft works.
</P>
<P>
The root of the wild rice stem is a delicacy for southern
Chinese, but the leaves are usually discarded.
</P>
<P>
The fragrant, green and rubbery leaves are good material for
knitting flying birds, walking animals, flowers and fish, said Xu
Weili and Qian Yongchang, who work at the Qingpu Foreign Trade
Company at Liantang Township, in Qingpu County. They invented
their unusual method last year.
</P>
<P>
The handicrafts became an immediate hit on the Japanese market,
and are expected to produce 760,000 yuan's worth of foreign
currency earnings this year.
</P>
<P>
The technique has been patented at China's Patent Office.
</P>
