<HEADLINE> China Sees Sharp Improvement in Engineering and Housing Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- China has greatly improved the
quality of various engineering and housing projects, due to the
effective implementation of the engineering supervision and
monitoring system nationwide.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference on engineering quality here
today, vice-minister of construction Tan Qinglian said large
groups of China's key projects and large-sized urban public
facilities as well as nearly one billion sq m of newly-built
housing residences have come up to the advanced world standards or
reach the State-set targets in terms of construction quality.
</P>
<P>
A national survey on construction quality shows that the
qualification rate of the country's engineering and housing
projects has increased by 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, breakthroughs have been made in the planning,
designing and construction of the country's engineering and
housing projects and great headway achieved in protecting
environment and in completing the infrastructural facilities.
</P>
<P>
According to the senior official, more than 90 percent of
China's cities and counties have set up engineering quality
supervision stations, which cover 88 percent of the country's
construction projects.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the country's 29 provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions have practised the engineering monitoring
system, establishing a total of 1,500 construction monitoring
institutes, which effectively handled or prevented some 60,000
hidden construction hazards and troubles in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Despite the progress made in improving construction quality,
however, many loopholes still exist, particularly in the
construction of residential housing, the vice-minister said,
adding that much still needs to be done in this respect.  
</P>
</TEXT>
