<HEADLINE> S. Korea's Overseas Investments Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Overseas direct investments by
South Korea increased by nearly 50 percent, to 3.69 billion
U.S. dollars, in the first eight months this year, the Bank of
Korea said today.
</P>
<P>
The money was invested in 1,148 projects, 89 more than the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Small-and medium-sized firms saw their direct investments from
Korea reach 783.5 million dollars in 601 approved projects during
the period, amounting to increases respectively of 21.2 and 52.4
percent. Asia took 53.1 percent of the total investment, that
was, 1.96 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Direct investments in China, South Korea's largest investment
beneficiary abroad, amounted to 943 million dollars in 597
approved projects, accounting for 25.6 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2.87 billion dollars worth of overseas
direct investments in 907 projects were actually carried out.
</P>
<P>
As of the end of August this year, South Korea's cumulative
overseas direct investments approved had climbed to 16.85 billion
dollars in 7,235 projects. 
</P>
