<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Hunan Province in central China
has recorded good harvests during the past 10 years, thanks to a
province-wide "Harvest Program".
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, over the past decade, Hunan produced
an additional 5.16 million tons of grain, 85,000 tons of cotton,
201,800 tons of rapeseed, 216,500 tons of livestock and poultry,
and 218,200 tons of fruits and vegetables.
</P>
<P>
Total agricultural output value was increased by 4.59 billion
yuan (about 573 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The goal of the "Harvest Program" is to promote agricultural
development by using advanced technology in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Hunan invested more than 1.6 billion yuan (some 200 million US
dollars) in developing 458 projects in rice, corn, sweet potato,
cotton, vegetable, fruit, and rapeseed production, and aquatic
products and livestock.
</P>
<P>
It implemented the "Harvest Program" in 78 counties and has
produced an additional 1.865 million tons of rice and 1.44 billion
yuan in agricultural output value.  
