<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Posts and
Telecommunications, the watchdog of China's telecommunications
business, is to build a 700-km-long microwave telecom trunk
between Xi'an and Chengdu, two major cities in western China.
</P>
<P>
The contract for the project has been signed between the
ministry, Posts and Telecom Equipment Corporation, and Fujitsu, a
leading telecom supplier of Japan, according to "People's Posts
and Telecommunications News".
</P>
<P>
The lastest SDH equipment of Fujitsu will be installed in the
project. When completed, the digital microwave trunk will add
more than 10,000 telephone lines to telecom links between the two
cities.
</P>
<P>
The trunk is the first national-level microwave project the
Japanese company has ever won in China, the paper said. Fujitsu
will transfer its SDH equipment to China by the end of this year.
