<HEADLINE> Young Man to Receive Ear Transplant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- A 25-year-old worker from East
China's Zhejiang Province recently underwent surgery to receive
articial ear implants in the Beijing-based Union Medical College
Hospital, according to "Health News."
</P>
<P>
Doctors performed an initial surgery to cut through a swelling
on the patient's ear, in order to implant three "nails" under his
skin that would attach to the man-made ear. A second surgery to
implant the ear is expected to be performed in the next three
months, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The paper cited professor Wang Dayuan as saying that this is
the first time for Chinese doctors to implant an ear for a patient
with a congenital malformation.
</P>
<P>
He said doctors at the hospital currently have a good command
of the technology of artificial tooth implants, and they have now
expanded the technique to other parts of the body, including eyes,
ears, nose and fingers, he said.  
