for students seeking Master's degree will be jointly launched by
the University of Macao (UOM) and Beijing University soon.
</P>
<P>
The joint course for some 20 people will be started at the UOM,
and has attracted more than 60 applicants.
</P>
<P>
Experts with the Chinese Language Department of the UOM said
that the course will meet the demand for personnel with a higher
level of Chinese language as Chinese is increasingly widely used
in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Enrolled students will study either linguistics or literature
and related subjects in the course, which lasts at least two
years. They are also required to compose a graduation thesis
before finishing their studies.
</P>
<P>
Beijing University and the UOM have cooperative relations for
over ten years. The new course is expected to improve the Chinese
language teaching at the UOM, experts said.
</P>
