<DOCNO> XIE19961004.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korea's Overseas Direct Investments Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, October 4 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's overseas direct
investments amounted to 3.69 billion U.S. dollars in 1,148
projects on an approval basis in the first eight months of this
year, said the Bank of Korea today.
</P>
<P>
The number of approved investment projects increased by 89
cases from the same period last year with the investment amounts
surging 1.19 billion dollars, the central bank said.
</P>
<P>
The overseas direct investments by small- and medium-sized
firms during the January-August period totaled 783.5 million
dollars in 601 cases on an approval basis, representing 21.2
percent and 52.4 percent respectively in terms of volume and
number of investment projects.
</P>
<P>
By region, Asia took up 53.1 percent or 1.96 billion dollars of
the total investments.
</P>
<P>
Direct investments in China, South Korea's largest investment
place abroad, amounted to 943 million dollars in 597 cases,
representing 25.6 percent and 52 percent in volume and number
respectively, the bank said.
</P>
<P>
During the eight months, a total of 2.87 billion dollars worth
of overseas direct investments in 907 projects were actually
carried out, up 30 cases and 863 million dollars in the number of
projects and investment amount from the same period of 1995.
</P>
<P>
As of the end of August this year, South Korea's cumulative
overseas direct investments approved had climbed to 16.85 billion
dollars in 7,235 projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
