<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK SAR Preparatory Committee Members Meet in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Two proposed methods for
selecting candidates of the first Hong Kong SAR Chief Executive
and the Provisional Legislative Council will be examined at the
fifth plenary session of the Preparatory Committee of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), which opened today in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The Preparatory Committee members will also discuss
qualifications of Selection Committee candidates, whose tasks are
to choose the Chief Executive and the Provisional Legislative
Council members.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the two-day meeting, Qian
Qichen, vice-premier of the State Council and chairman of the
Preparatory Committee, said that the two documents submitted to
the group for examination are of great importance.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong people and the world community are greatly
concerned about the selection process of the first Chief Executive
and the Provisional Legislative Council, he added.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that the two suggested methods conform completely to
the Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR, the relevant decisions of the
National People's Congress and of the Preparatory Committee, and
also to the principles of openness, fairness and justice, and are
feasible and applicable.
</P>
<P>
As for choosing the candidates for the Chief Executive, he said
the Selection Committee has been entrusted with full rights at
every stage of the process, from nomination to election.
</P>
<P>
The method for forming the Provisional Legislative Council also
reflects the universal aspiration of the Hong Kong society,
namely, that those who meet the relevant requirements are capable
of taking part in the election, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
During the opening session, Qian also reviewed the work of the
Preparatory Committee after the fourth plenary session held nearly
two months ago.
</P>
<P>
He said the Preparatory Committee did not expect so many people
to apply to be Selection Committee members, which shows that the
Hong Kong people are enthusiastic about preparing for the
establishment of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
"Meanwhile, it demonstrates that the Hong Kong people are
confident and capable of handling well the affairs of Hong Kong,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Work reports from the first Chief Executive Panel and the
Provisional Legislative Council Panel were presented at the
meeting, which is being held in the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
Lu Ping, vice-chairman and secretary-general of the Preparatory
Committee, briefed participants on the application process for the
Selection Committee membership, and explained the two proposals
for the selection process.
</P>
<P>
Henry Ying Tung Fok, vice-chairman of the Preparatory Committee,
presided over the opening ceremony.  
</P>
</TEXT>
