<HEADLINE> Vietnam Joins ASEAN Tourism Association </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnamese General Department
of Tourism (VGDT) has become a full member of the ASEAN Tourism
Association (ASEANTA), local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
Its admission to ASEANTA would create new opportunities for the
Vietnamese tourist service to integrate into, and cooperate with,
other member states of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
In recent years, VGDT has established close relations with
international tourist organizations such as the Pacific Area
Travel Association (PATA), the Japanese Tourist Association (JATA)
and the American Society of Travel Agents (ASTA).
</P>
<P>
ASEANTA was established in march 1971 and now has more than 60
members including tourist services, hotel owners, transport
companies, airlines and state-run offices in charge of tourism
from ASEAN member states as well as countries out of the
organization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
