<HEADLINE> Share Price Index Keeps Falling on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Share prices finished mixed on
the Singapore market while the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index continued to go down, losing another 1.9 points to close at
2,148.86 today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 113.76 million units, valued
at 251.03 million Singapore dollars (about 179.31 million US
dollars). Advances led declines by 151 to 131, while 299 other
counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Nippecraft was the most actively traded counter as it posted a
turnover of 12.36 million units. It was followed by Pacific Andes
which had 8.11 million shares traded. Dairy Farm was next with
5.49 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Oriental Holdings led the gainers of the day as it rose by
40 cents to finish at 11.9 Singapore dollars. Hong Leong Credit
was next, picking up 30 cents to end at 7.7 Singapore dollars,
while the Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation (OCBC) Foreign
gained 20 cents to 16.8 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, OU Trust Foreign was the biggest loser as it
declined 1.7 Singapore dollars to close at 2.2 Singapore dollars.
Asean 100 fell one dollars to nine US dollars, while Creative 50
finished 50 cents lower at 8.05 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
