<HEADLINE> China Welcomes Removal of Sanctions Against Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government welcomes
the unanimous resolution made recently by the UN Security Council
to remove the sanctions against the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia, Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Shen Guofang said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Shen said the sanctions, which have been in place for several
years, have done nothing to settle problems, and have brought only
great disaster to the Yugoslavian people.
</P>
<P>
"In international relations, we have always been opposed to
constantly imposing sanctions against a country, and have made
unremitting efforts for removing the sanctions against Yugoslavia
soon," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"The resolution of the Security Council shows that the policy
of peace pursued by Yugoslavia has been widely recognized by the
entire international community," he added.
</P>
<P>
The removal of the sanctions will not only be helpful to the
economic development of Yugoslavia, but will promote the peace
process of the former Yugoslavia region and even peace and
stability in Europe, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the international community will consider, as
soon as possible, the proper solution of the issue of Yugoslavia's
status in the UN and other international organizations," Shen
noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
