<HEADLINE> Displaced Families To Be Resettled In Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 4 (Xinhua)-- Families displaced from the
districts of Jaffna and Mannar in Northern province of Sri Lanka
due to separatist insurgency will be resettled in Puttalam,
rehabilitation and construction ministry sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the ministry has made all arrangements
for the resettlement program which commences on October 5.
</P>
<P>
At least 6,000 displaced people (1,350 families) will be
resettled in two model villages in Puttalam district.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the ministry has allocated 241,100 US
dollars for this resettlement program and 223,000 US dollars for
infrastructure facilities.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the resettlement program, the ministry will open
several new school buildings already completed for the benefit of
children in Puttalam district.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that each family will be given dry ration
worth 22.5 US dollars per month, up to six months by the ministry.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
