<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Growing Number of Mobile Phone Users in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Anhui Province had 100,857
mobile phone users by September 18, making it one of the leading
mobile telephone consumers in China, according to "People's Posts
and Telecommunications News".
</P>
<P>
The province's analog mobile telecommunications network has
expanded for the sixth time, giving it a switching capacity of
180,000 sets, 106 base stations, and 3,700 channels.
</P>
<P>
A first-phase expansion project for the province's GSM (global
service for mobile communication) network, which was completed a
few months ago, has added a switching capacity of 5,000 sets and
49 base stations.
</P>
<P>
A second-phase project for the GSM network is now under
way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
