<HEADLINE> Historical City Attracts Business with Places of Interests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The historic city of Yangzhou in
east China's Jiangsu Province is making use of its places of
interests to attract business people.
</P>
<P>
During a ten-day sightseeing and trade activity, which began on
September 26, the city opened a travel route from the Royal Wharf,
to the Shouxi Lake, Daming Monastery and Pingshan Hall.
</P>
<P>
Art performances were arranged in over 20 halls and also
waterfront pavilions. Visitors can also enjoy a moonlight ride in
a dragon boat.
</P>
<P>
During the Mid-Autumn Festival, the city held an exhibition to
display automobiles, motor vehicles, machinery, electronics,
textiles, building materials, household electronics, and sports
goods.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 100 enterprises from 14 countries and regions attended
the exhibition. During the show, the city offered 250 projects for
discussion with overseas business people.
</P>
<P>
By September 27, business people from the United States and
Australia had signed 21 projects with the city, with a total
investment of 90 million US dollars.  
</P>
