<HEADLINE> Foreign Investors Flocking to Hengshui in Hebei Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investors are
flocking to Hengshui, in north China's Hebei Province, with the
completion of the Beijing-Kowloon Railway.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Hengshui city government said that since
the beginning of this year, Hengshui has signed 172 economic
cooperation contracts with overseas companies, involving 21.52
million US dollars in overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The official said that Hengshui is a hub on the Beijing-Kowloon
Railway Line, as it links transport in northeast China, north
China, east China and south China.
</P>
<P>
Wang Menghui, an economist and director of the State Council
Policy Research Center, said that Hengshui has become the nearest
transport hub to Beijing on the Beijing-Kowloon Railway.
</P>
<P>
"Hengshui has entered into the period of the fastest economic
growth and with the best development environment," he said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, Hengshui has speeded up infrastructure
construction in a move to improve its investment environment. For
example, the Hengshui Power plant, with a generating capacity of
1.2 million kilowatts, has been completed.
</P>
<P>
A canal that diverts water from the Yellow River to Hengshui
also is in operation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
