<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Germany's top seed Steffi Graf
and fourth-seeded Anke Huber advanced to the semifinals on
Thursday at the $450,000 Leipzig Tennis tournament in Germany.
</P>
<P>
Graf, who is appearing in her first tournament since capturing
her fifth U.S. Open tennis championship three weeks ago, struggled
to a 1-6, 6-3, 6-2 victory over Austrian Judith Wiesner.
</P>
<P>
Huber will meet Graf in the semifinals thanks to a 6-4, 7-6
(7-5) decision over sixth seed Magdalena Maleeva of Bulgaria.
</P>
