<HEADLINE> East China Economic Zone Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Xiaoshan Economic and
Technological Development Zone in Xiaoshan County, Zhejiang
Province, which was established three years ago, now has 107
overseas-funded companies in it.
</P>
<P>
A member of the Zone Administrative Commission said that 40
percent of the companies are wholly-owned overseas businesses,
involving 427 million US dollars in overseas investment, and that
17 companies developed for Chinese and foreign investors, have at
least 10 million dollars in investment each.
</P>
<P>
He said that the investors are from 20 countries and regions in
Asia, north America, and Eastern and Western Europe.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, the leading manufacturing and port city in China, is
only 90 minutes away by car, thanks to an expressway, as is Ningbo
Port. And the provincial capital of Hangzhou is only ten minutes
away.
</P>
<P>
In the past three years, Xiaoshan County, one of the most
developed counties in China, has spent 2.5 billion yuan on
infrastructure, and 500 million yuan on infrastructure in the
zone. Construction of an international airport will begin in
Xiaoshan soon. 
