<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines' Inflation Rate Drops to 4.4 in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- the Philippine National
Statistics Office announced here today that the country's
inflation rate dropped to 4.4 percent in September this year, the
lowest since July 1987.
</P>
<P>
The office said by regions Metro Manila registered a 6.3
percent inflation rate during the month, 1.6 percentage points
lower than August's 7.9 percent. The rate for areas outside Metro
Manila moved down to 3.7 percent from 7.8 percent in August.
</P>
<P>
The drop was mainly due to falling prices of major commodities
and services in the country. The commodities include food,
beverage and tobacco, fuel, electricity and water.
</P>
<P>
the country's inflation rate went up to double digits in
September last year as a result of the rice crisis, but it
returned to single digit last June and has been declining for four
consecutive months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
