<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rong Yiren Meets with Polish Procuratorial Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Rong
Yiren told a senior Polish official today that he hopes China's
legal system can be improved through exchanges with foreign
judicial and procuratorial circles.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with a Polish procuratorial delegation headed
by its Minister of Justice Leszek Kubicki, Rong pointed out that
China and Poland share a long history of friendly ties, that
relations between the two countries in various fields have enjoyed
constant development over the past few years, and that there have
been increasing visits by leaders from both sides.
</P>
<P>
"A good cooperative relation also exists between the judicial
and procuratorial circles of the two countries," Rong noted.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes that Kubicki's current visit will promote
understanding, friendship and cooperation between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president also briefed the guests on China's economic
development and legal system construction, adding that China makes
its laws according to its own situation. He said he hopes that
China's legal system will be improved through exchanges with
foreign countries in these areas.
</P>
<P>
Kubicki, also Poland's prosecutor-general, said the judicial
and procuratorial circles of both countries are now faced with the
same or similar problems, and that he hopes exchanges and
cooperation between the two sides be increased in this area.
</P>
<P>
Kubicki and his party arrived here this morning for a 3-day
good-will visit as guests of Zhang Siqing, procurator-general of
the Supreme People's Procuratorate. 
</P>
