<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Third Largest Trade Partner of Island Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Imports and exports between Japan
and Hainan, China's southernmost island province, registered a
16 percent increase in the first seven months of this year,
reaching 150 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Japan has become Hainan's third-largest trade partner, after
Hong Kong and Russia.
</P>
<P>
Hainan's trade with Japan accounted for nine percent of its
total external trade in the first seven months. Exports to Japan
made up 17 percent of its total, representing a 5.2 percent rise.
</P>
<P>
State owned enterprises have been the backbone of the bilateral
trade development. They contributed 80 percent of exports to and
imports from Japan in the first seven months.
</P>
<P>
Exports from overseas-funded enterprises increased
23-fold over the same period of last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
