<HEADLINE> Brisk Processing Trade In Chinese Island Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, October 4 (Xinhua) -- South China's island province of
Hainan generated 77.69 million US dollars in processing materials
supplied by overseas customers in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
This was a 64 percent increase over the same period of last
year, according to customs statistics released here recently.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-funded processing enterprises in Hainan exported 39.38
million US dollars worth of products in the first half of the
year, a 79 percent rise over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The figure surpassed the export value from state owned
enterprises for the first time in the history of these companies.
</P>
<P>
In addition to their increased output, processing firms have
shortened the delivery time and improved their capacity for more
detailed processing.  
</P>
