<DOCNO> XIE19961004.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Constitutional Amendment Passed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 4 (Xinhua) --Zimbabwean Parliament Thursday
unanimously passed the 14th amendment to the Zimbabwean
constitution which will enhance gender equality, guarantee more
protection to the property of foreign investors and ensure the
protection of human rights.
</P>
<P>
The bill amends chapter 11 of the constitution, which mainly
deals with citizenship.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the amendment, only foreign wives of Zimbabwean men
had automatic citizenship rights, while foreign husbands of
indigenous women could only be granted citizenship when they were
approved as investors or as holders of scarce skills.
</P>
<P>
However, under the new amendment, limits will be placed on the
right of all foreigners married to Zimbabwean citizens to enter
and live in Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
The amendment will protect the rights guaranteed to foreign
investors and other people under international treaties and
conventions to which Zimbabwe is a party. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
