<HEADLINE> Improved Airline Service For Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Tourism on the lush grasslands
and cool weather of Inner Mongolia in northern China, which has
increased but been hampered by inconvenient transport conditions,
has gotten a boost from Air China.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, rapid expansion of service by Air China, the
country's flag carrier, has made the grassland more accessible to
tourists from neighboring provinces and regions as well as other
countries.
</P>
<P>
The airline branch for Inner Mongolia has more than 30 routes,
and takes less than three hours to get to Hohhot, capital of the
region, from Guangzhou, Harbin, Shanghai and Kunming.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that more than 1,000 people pass through
Hohhot's airport each day, and almost every flight is packed
full.  
</P>
