<DOCNO> XIE19961004.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China Coastal Real Estate Market Regaining Strength </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIHAI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The real estate market in the
south China city of Beihai was back on its feet again in the
third quarter of the year, after having gone through a sluggish
period.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 deals, worth 424.8 million yuan (about 51 million
US dollars), have been struck since June in the coastal city's
property market, which has been a barometer in the country's real
estate business. This was the highest in the past two years.
</P>
<P>
To improve the ailing real estate market and turn it into a
pillar of local economy, the city implemented a series of methods
this May to reclaim parcels of land that had been leased
improperly or in excessive amounts, and to standardize the
market. As a result, it has recovered 10.86 square kilometers of
land, providing more opportunities for property development.
</P>
<P>
It has also reduced taxes by 550 million yuan (about 66 million
US dollars) to help nearly 1,000 property developers get out of
difficulties.
</P>
<P>
These policies have had an immediate impact on the real estate
business. One transaction alone was responsible for the sale of
14,000 square meters of flats.
</P>
<P>
Since June, a group of real estate agencies have begun to
increase their investment. Additional investment in the city's
largest property project, the Hengli Ocean Sports Vacationing
Center, hit 25 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Analysts also attribute the boom in Beihai's real estate market
to the Nanning-Kunming Railway line, which passes nearby and is
expected to open soon, and to the impending return of Hong Kong to
the motherland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
