<HEADLINE> India's Congress Party Postpones Party Polls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- India's Congress Party
President Sitaram Kesri Thursday postponed the party's
organization polls by extending the last date of enrollment of new
members till November 15, the Hindustan Times said today.
</P>
<P>
Under the new poll schedule, the election for a new All India
Congress Committee (AICC) president will take place on March 12
and the results will be announced five days later.
</P>
<P>
Kesri succeeded P.V. Narasimha Rao as AICC president as the
latter resigned over his involvement in a cheating case last
month.
</P>
<P>
The earlier poll program had envisaged the completion of
enrollment of new party members by September 30. Under the
program announced Thursday by Kesri, the electoral rolls will be
published on January 25.
</P>
<P>
The new members, along with the existing members, will form the
electoral college that will elect a new AICC president as well as
other office bearers at the district and the state level.
</P>
<P>
The organizational polls are considered a major test of
strength of various Congress Party groups which are keen to ensure
their nominees bag coveted posts in the party hierarchy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
