<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former WBA Champ Charged with Cocaine Possession </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Former WBA heavyweight
champion Tony Tubbs has been charged with possession of crack
cocaine.
</P>
<P>
Accoding to a press report, Police said Tubbs was found in a
car early Thursday a rock of crack on the floor near one of his
feet.
</P>
<P>
The charge is a fifth-degree felony, punishable by up to a year
in prison and a dlrs 2,500 fine, police said.
</P>
<P>
At Tubbs' initial appearance in Hamilton County Municipal Court
on Thursday, Judge Dennis Helmick agreed with Tubbs' attorney that
there was little evidence to show the crack belonged to the
boxer. Helmick released Tubbs after he promised to return for
other court hearings.
</P>
<P>
Tubbs last fought professionally in August 1995, losing to
Alexander Zolkin in a 12-round decision in Atlantic City, New
Jersey.
</P>
<P>
He won the WBA title with a 15-round decision over Greg Page in
1986. He lost the title eight months later in a decision to Tim
Witherspoon.
</P>
<P>
Tubbs, 38, of Cincinnati, could not be reached for comment late
Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
