<HEADLINE> India to Host International Crop Science Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
new Delhi, October 4 (Xinhua) -- India will host the
prestigious 2nd international crop science congress (ICSC) from
November 17 to 24, the Hindustan Times said today.
</P>
<P>
Doctor R.S Paroda from India's Department of Agricultural
Research and Education said at a press conference here that the
significance of the meeting lay in the fact that, despite
phenomenal growth in food production, about 20 percent of the
world population was still hungry and malnourished.
</P>
<P>
He said diminishing per capita availability of land and water
resources coupled with land, forest and environmental degradation
further intensified the challenges and he called for greater
resolve on the part of agriculture scientists to ensure synergism
among productivity, profitability and sustainability of major
cropping system.
</P>
<P>
Paroda said for safeguarding food and nutrition security at the
household level, crop intensification and diversification were
needed on an ecologically sustainable basis.
</P>
<P>
The new tools of genetic engineering, germplasm enhancement and
crop modeling offered new opportunities for producing better
plants, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the 2nd ICSC would deliberate on the subjects to
provide directions for a new agenda for crop science research
during 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the congress was "crop productivity and
sustainability: shaping the future," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
