<HEADLINE> IDB Loans $15 Million to Honduras for Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank today announced the approval of a 15 million-
U.S.-dollar soft loan to Honduras for an agricultural improvement
program.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be used as part of a fund to finance the
development and transfer of technology for agriculture, as well as
training for workers involved in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the program is 17 million dollars. The IDB
soft loan is for a 40-year term, with a 10-year grace period, at
an annual interest rate of one percent during the grace period and
two percent thereafter.
</P>
<P>
The IDB has so far this year approved a total of 244.8 million
dollars to finance global agriculture. 
</P>
