<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Airlines Boosts Market Share </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam Airlines has boosted its
market share by 12 percent after four years of extensive
restructuring, the local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The market share of the state-owned Vietnam Airlines rose from
31 percent in 1991 to more than 43 percent this year, in the
presence of 24 foreign airlines in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The airlines began to undergo a facelift to improve its fleet
which mainly consisted of Soviet-made aircraft since 1992.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the airlines carried more than 2.25 million passengers
and 33,000 tons of cargo, more than five times higher than that of
1991, a report of the Vietnam Airlines said.
</P>
<P>
In the first eight months of 1996, the airlines transported
over 1.7 million passengers including 700,000 foreigners and
28,200 tons of cargo, representing 80.4 percent of the yearly
target.
</P>
<P>
So far, seven out of the ten airbus 320s leased by Vietnam
Airlines have arrived in this country. The Vietnam Airlines plans
to have a completely new fleet of western aircraft within five
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
