<HEADLINE> International Science Cooperation In East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang Province in east China
is planning to increase investment in international science
cooperation over the next five years, focusing on computers,
electronics, new materials, new energy resources, energy saving
technology, biology, and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The province already has co-operation in science with more than
40 countries and regions, and has had 181 international projects
during the past five years, the majority of which have had good
results, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
A flood monitoring and forecast system, established with the
European Union, has improved local ability to monitor and predict
flooding in the Fuchun River, one of the largest rivers in the
province.
</P>
<P>
The system has helped avoid more than one billion yuan in
economic losses, officials say.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of the year, science research institutes and
scientists in the province have submitted plans for more than 50
projects for international cooperation in agriculture, industry,
and medicine. 
</P>
