<HEADLINE> Floods Death Toll Rises to 34 in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Floods continue to wreak havoc
in at least 34 of Thailand's 76 provinces, bringing the death toll
to 34 since last month.
</P>
<P>
The Civil Disaster Prevention Office said floods have affected
1.7 million people and damaged more than 64,000 hectares of
farmland.
</P>
<P>
Damage is estimated at 909 million baht (36.36 million US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Flash floods have struck many provinces nationwide,
particularly the central plains.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Interior Ministry is to ask the care-taker
cabinet for a 800 million baht (32 million US dollars) emergency
fund for flood relief.
</P>
<P>
Bangkok governor Bhichit Rattakul Thursday inspected watergates
in eastern Bangkok to ensure that they were in working order.
Eastern Bangkok is low-lying and often suffers floods.
</P>
<P>
City workers were also working hard to strengthen embankments
in flood-prone areas and to control water volume.  
</P>
</TEXT>
