<HEADLINE> Graf Enters Semis in Leipzig Tennis Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 3 (Xinhua) -- German Steffi Graf rallied from a
first set deficit to beat Austrian Judith Wiesner in three sets,
booking her semifinal spot in the Leipzig Open on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In 450,000 US dollars tournament where five of seven world top
players compete, Graf survived a big scare to overcome Wiesner
1-6, 6-3 and 6-2.
</P>
<P>
For Graf, it was the worst experience, her first tournament in
home turf after her father went on trial for tax evasion, since
her opponent ranked 20 places below and lost all previous 10 meets.
</P>
<P>
With her hard win after conceding the first set in 26 minutes,
Graf faces compatriot fourth-seeded Anke Huber in Saturday's
semifinal.
</P>
<P>
Huber, defending champion, defeated sixth-seeded Magdalena
Maleeva of Bulgaria 6-4 and 7-6 (8-6).
</P>
<P>
Second seed Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario reached the quarterfinals
by routing Mariam Oremans of the Netherlands 6-2 and 6-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
