<HEADLINE> Woodruff Exits From Lyon Grand Prix Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 3 (Xinhua) -- American Chris Woodruff made his
exit after losing to Frenchman Lionel Roux in the Lyon Grand Prix
tennis tournament on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Woodruff who beat top seed Thomas Muster the night before, was
defeated by Roux 3-6, 7-6 (7-5) and 7-5, with the latter moving
into the last eight of the 750,000 US dollars tournament.
</P>
<P>
Woodruff had an easy win of the first set in half a hour before
a tiebreaker in the second set where he lost 5-7.
</P>
<P>
In the decider, Roux broke Woodruff in the seventh game for a
4-3 lead before Woodruff managed for 5-5 deadlock.
</P>
<P>
However, the American dropped the 11th game with double fault
and Roux served to his victory of 7-5 in two hours 39 minutes.
</P>
<P>
In other second round matches, Tim Henman of Britain outlasted
Jan Siemerink of Netherlands 6-7 (4-7), 7-6 (7-3) 7-6 (7-5), and
Slovakia Karol Kucera defeated Moroccan Younes El Aynaoui 7-5 and
6-2.
</P>
<P>
Arnaud Boetsch of France sailed further as Russian Andrei
Chessnokov retired in the second set with a leg injury. 
