<HEADLINE> Cuban Arab Leader Warns Israel of Popular Uprising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Alfredo Deriche, president of the
Arab Union of Cuba, warned today that a popular uprising will
become a choice for the Palestinians with all the roads to peace
closed by Israel.
</P>
<P>
The government of Israel "does not want to exchange land for
peace, because it does not want peace and it does not want to
return the land either," said Deriche.
</P>
<P>
Deriche's remarks came after Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu met Tuesday and
Wednesday in Washington without settling their differences after
the recent bloodshed in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Arafat and Netanyahu were expected to resume their talks on
Sunday to reach a preliminary agreement of peace in the Middle
East.
</P>
<P>
The Arab Union of Cuba, created in 1979, is calling for a
symposium next week on the Arab presence in America, which will be
attended by 30 foreign experts and the same number of Cuban
scholars.
</P>
<P>
The three major topics to be discussed at the symposium will be
Arab immigration in America, Arab language and literature, and art
and Islam. 
