<HEADLINE> Two Channel Ferries to Merge, 1,000 Jobs at Risk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Up to 1,000 jobs are at risk
after Britain's P&AMP;O European Ferries and Sweden's Stena Line
announced today that they plan to merge their short distance
Channel ferry businesses between Britain and France, according to
a BBC TV report.
</P>
<P>
The move comes amid fierce competition from the Channel Tunnel,
which has taken over a third of cross-Channel traffic on the most
popular Dover-Calais route.
</P>
<P>
The new firm, P&AMP;O Stena line, will operate on the Dover-Calais,
Newhaven-Dieppe and Dover to Zeebrugge routes.
</P>
<P>
P&AMP;O will hold 60 percent of the shares in the new firm, while
Stena takes 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
"The new company will offer more vigorous competition to
Eurotunnel and improved scheduling, as well as maintaining the
present high standards on the existing ferry services and
providing for eventual future investment," the companies said in a
joint statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
